No, I think you need to take the other factors into account.  Because the base damage of FoT is higher, it means your DD bracer can increase more, it means SCF-3 ability can increase more.  And if you are Evoc instead of Conj specilized, it gives FoT another advantage.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, if you are SCM-3, Conj spec, you'll do better using black steel.<br>
<br>
There is a nice DD comparison chart sticky above, look at the Damage per Mana one (not the DPS one which clearly FoT wins).<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Baron Zacatac Soulwanderer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zacatac>Zacatac</A> at: 2/26/03 5:28:57 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=salashpenumbra>Salash Penumbra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 431<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/03 8:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1859.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Black Steel changed ??</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Because the base damage of FoT is higher, it means your DD bracer can increase more, it means SCF-3 ability can increase more. And if you are Evoc instead of Conj specilized, it gives FoT another advantage.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
All that actually makes NO difference at all when comparing the 2 spells (except spec) as all those effects are percentage based.<br>
<br>
If you add 10% to one thing, and 10% to another, and then compare them to each other they're exactly the same (relativly) because the bonuses cancel each other out. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=38898">Salash Penumbra</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower">Summoner</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.midnightfury.org">Armies</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=matthiuscinderfist>Matthius Cinderfist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/03 9:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1859.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Black Steel changed ??</span><hr size=1> I think what he was trying to say is that with a Focus Bracer and/or SCF, the difference between FBoT dmg/mana + dps and Black Steel dmg/mana + dps increases, with FBoT coming out on top in both dmg/mana and dps. <br>
<br>
This means that Bracer and/or SCF has a greater impact(dmg/mana and dps) with FBoT than Bracer and/or SCF with Black Steel. Those factors make a difference; just based on SCF alone, you double the difference in efficiency between FBoT and Black Steel for base vs. crit. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20616">Sage Matthius Cinderfist</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Shorty Arch Convoker of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/bforlorn"> Forlorn</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=matthiuscinderfist>Matthius Cinderfist</A> at: 2/26/03 9:15:11 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xalmatelemental>XalmatElemental</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/03 9:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1859.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Black Steel changed ??</span><hr size=1> A bit lost on the argument. So I'm going to take the indifferent route, and lay the facts.<br>
<br>
Assuming level 65, no Spell Casting Mastery, no Spell Casting Fury, no foci (SCM complicates things. Damage and cast time foci/abilities make no difference for comparison sake). Adjusting for 2.25 recast time on all spells for sustained DPS. Ignoring travel time for the bolt aspect of Firebolt of Tallon, since it is highly dependent on distance from target.<br>
<br>
Also assuming 50 specialized = 2.5% mana preserve, 200 specialized = 10% mana preserve. Forget where this figure comes from.<br>
<br>
For all calculations, rounding to three decimal places.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Base</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Firebolt of Tallon - 2000 damage, 500 mana, 7 second cast. 4 dmg/mana, 285.7 instant DPS, 216.2 sustained DPS.<br>
Black Steel - 1400 damage, 360 mana, 6.25 second cast. 3.888 dmg/mana, 224 instant DPS, 164.7 sustained DPS.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Evocation Specialized</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (10% preserve on Evocation, 2.5% on Conjuration)<br>
Firebolt of Tallon - 2000 damage, 450 mana. 4.444 dmg/mana<br>
Black Steel - 1400 damage, 351 mana. 3.989 dmg/mana<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Conjuration Specialized</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (10% preserve on Conjuration, 2.5% on Evocation)<br>
Firebolt of Tallon - 2000 damage, 487.5 mana. 4.102 dmg/mana<br>
Black Steel - 1400 damage, 324 mana. 4.321 dmg/mana<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Conclusion</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Given the above assumptions...<br>
Firebolt of Tallon has more sustained DPS than Black Steel, regardless of specialization.<br>
Ignoring Specialization, Firebolt of Tallon is more mana efficient than Black Steel.<br>
For the Evocation Specialized mage, Firebolt of Tallon is more mana efficient than Black Steel.<br>
For the Conjuration Specialized mage, Black Steel is more mana efficient than Firebolt of Tallon. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=204546" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.marksmans.com/images/xalsig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xalmatelemental>XalmatElemental</A> at: 2/26/03 9:31:07 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zacatac>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1809<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/03 9:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1859.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Black Steel changed ??</span><hr size=1> Well you're right, I didn't phrase that correctly.  It's more the DPS difference than DPM.<br>
<br>
2000 vs. 1400 non-focus'd<br>
4400 vs. 3080 max dmg w/focus bracer and SCF-3 crit<br>
<br>
The nukes start at 600 dmg difference, but end up 1320 difference.  <br>
<br>
But the DPM comparison is the roughly the same because the factors increase on both sides of the equation and &quot;wash out&quot;.<br>
<br>
(not using SCM or spec. for comparison)<br>
<br>
FoT<br>
(2000*1.20) + 2000 =  4400 at level 65 with bracer. <br>
4400 dmg / 500 mana = 8.8  on max nuke<br>
<br>
BS<br>
(1400*1.20) + 1400 = 3080 at level 65 with bracer.<br>
3080 dmg / 360 mana = 8.56 on max nuke<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Baron Zacatac Soulwanderer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goladus>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Poobah Goladus</span><br>  Posts: 2746<br> <font color=#333333>(2/27/03 3:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1859.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://doug.feldmann.com/Sigurd.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Black Steel changed ??</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I thought it was significantly more efficient than FoT (before specializations are taken into account) . <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Nope.  In terms of Damage per Mana and Damage per Cast Time, Firebolt of Tallon is the best nuke we get.  Damage per Aggro is hard to measure.<br>
<br>
The issue is that FoT is a bolt.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>With</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Conjuration Specialization, I believe Black Steel will come out ahead of FoT.  However with no specialization FoT does have better stats, if you discount that it is a bolt. <p><center><br>
