<br>
Lets take a simple example (assume 2s refresh time):<br>
FastCast spell: 650dmg / 1s cast time<br>
SlowCast spell: 2000dmg / 8s cast time<br>
<br>
Without focus:<br>
FastCast max dps = 217dmg/s (3s total cast time)<br>
SlowCast max dps = 200dmg/s (10s total cast time)<br>
<br>
With Focus (15% ring + 10% BoR for example):<br>
FastCast max dps = 236dmg/s (2.75s total cast time)<br>
SlowCast max dps = 250dmg/s (8s total cast time)<br>
<br>
If we wish to consider sustained DPS, then we can also add the effect of specialization (not SCM) in, as this CAN differenciate two spells. However, if the spells use the same spec, then this too can be ignored.<br>
<br>
Conclusion:<br>
DPM comparison - only consider Spec<br>
DPS comparison - only consider Spell Haste, and Spec for sustained long term dps for different spell types.<br>
<br>
